<title id="_6c9cf665-3e05-929b-092e-3043ef6a2fcc">The relation between the numbers <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(M)_r</asciimath></stem> and <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>B</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(B)_j</asciimath></stem></title>
<p id="_9acad5fb-6d48-5b0b-5a8b-712df7cde80c">In our recent study <eref type="inline" bibitemid="muller" citeas="[1]"/> on alternate sums of powers of integers, i.e. of sums of the type</p>

<formula id="_56e9f469-b3ba-5e5e-c1b0-96224bdb5469" anchor="eq1"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="double-struck">
        <mi>Z</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>n</mi>
      </munderover>
      <msup>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mo>−</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>j</mi>
      </msup>
    </mrow>
    <msup>
      <mi>j</mi>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msup>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mtext> with </mtext>
    <mi>r</mi>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mn>1</mn>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mn>2</mn>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mo>…</mo>
    <mo>,</mo>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_rZZ_n = sum_(j=1)^n (-1)^j j^r, " with " r = 1,2,...,</asciimath></stem></formula>

<p id="_426a5884-6aa0-a7f3-a7f7-e08984555164">it was shown that they can be expressed in the form</p>

<formula id="_d6bd4b88-cc4b-8368-1fb3-ff0986614ff1" anchor="eq2"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="double-struck">
        <mi>Z</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow>
          <mi>r</mi>
          <mo>−</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
      </munderover>
      <msub>
        <mtext/>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </msub>
    </mrow>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>μ</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msub>
    <msup>
      <mi>t</mi>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msup>
    <mo>+</mo>
    <mfrac>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mn>2</mn>
    </mfrac>
    <msup>
      <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mo>−</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>)</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msup>
    <msup>
      <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo>)</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msup>
    <mo>,</mo>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_rZZ_n = sum_(j=1)^(r-1) ""_r ii(mu)_j t^j + 1/2 (-1)^n (2t)^r,</asciimath></stem></formula>

<p id="_770eacc9-51e0-94db-e0ca-d51926b6a5ee">where <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>t</mi>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mrow>
      <mo>[</mo>
      <mfrac>
        <mrow>
          <mi>n</mi>
          <mo>+</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mn>2</mn>
      </mfrac>
      <mo>]</mo>
    </mrow>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>t = [(n+1)/2]</asciimath></stem> is given by the number of terms in <xref target="eq1"/>, while <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>μ</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_r ii(mu)_j</asciimath></stem> are coefficients that have been tabulated.</p>

<p id="_5996e92b-94e3-065a-8aab-0fe79a39404c">We found that these coefficients can be expressed by the “basic” integers <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <mi>≡</mi>
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>μ</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>1</mn>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(M)_r -= ""_r ii(mu)_1</asciimath></stem>, since</p>

<formula id="_6bf53e32-8676-5eff-4803-e7406836a316" anchor="eq3"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>μ</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mfrac>
      <mrow>
        <msup>
          <mn>2</mn>
          <mrow>
            <mi>j</mi>
            <mo>−</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mi>!</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>!</mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mi>r</mi>
          <mo>−</mo>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>+</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>!</mi>
      </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mrow>
        <mi>r</mi>
        <mo>−</mo>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
      </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo>,</mo>
    <mtext> for </mtext>
    <mi>r</mi>
    <mo>&gt;</mo>
    <mi>j</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_r ii(mu)_j = (2^(j-1)r!)/(j!(r-j+1)!) ii(M)_(r-j+1)," for " r &gt; j</asciimath></stem></formula>

<p id="_4b8bab92-ff1e-59ad-0466-3604fa6f3120">The alternate sum <xref target="eq1"/>, written in powers of <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>t</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>t</asciimath></stem>, thus begins for <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>r</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>r</asciimath></stem> even with</p>

<formula id="_b1e1b986-7800-3031-15d8-9479a5cb5193" anchor="eq4"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="double-struck">
        <mi>Z</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <mi>t</mi>
    <mo>+</mo>
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>μ</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mn>2</mn>
    </msub>
    <msup>
      <mi>t</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
    </msup>
    <mo>+</mo>
    <mo>…</mo>
    <mo>,</mo>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_rZZ_n = ii(M)_rt + ""_r ii(mu)_2t^2 + ...,</asciimath></stem></formula>

<p id="_85dec4de-9ebf-7855-3f30-382ded896ea0">whereas for <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>r</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>r</asciimath></stem> odd there is no term proportional to <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>t</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>t</asciimath></stem>.</p>

<p id="_61bf5f61-e970-9fd0-49b1-f27e03c220e1">It appears that the numbers <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(M)_r</asciimath></stem> play a role similar to that of the well-known Bernoulli numbers <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>B</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(B)_j</asciimath></stem> which occur in the study of the sums</p>

<formula id="_cad68432-0d4d-ae37-5333-484a5b6af930" anchor="eq5"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>S</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
    <mi>≡</mi>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>n</mi>
      </munderover>
      <msup>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </msup>
    </mrow>
    <mo>.</mo>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_r ii(S)_n -= sum_(j=1)^n j^r.</asciimath></stem></formula>

<p id="_50104412-d6e4-3e90-1503-10cf92cf5b03">Some similarities between the numbers <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>B</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>j</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(B)_j</asciimath></stem> and <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(M)_r</asciimath></stem> have already been noted in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="muller" citeas="[1]"/>, but it has not been possible to establish a clear link between the two series. It is the purpose of the present Note to make up for this deficiency. Some familiarity with <eref type="inline" bibitemid="muller" citeas="[1]"/> will make the reading easier.</p>

<p id="_1ea0147a-93a0-1b57-8927-42894721fca1">The idea is to use the fact that the numbers <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>ii(M)_r</asciimath></stem> are the coefficients of <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>t</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>t</asciimath></stem>, as shown in <xref target="eq4"/>. If we can subdivide <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="double-struck">
        <mi>Z</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_rZZ_n</asciimath></stem> into a sum of contributions of type <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <mi>S</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_r ii(S)_n</asciimath></stem> and determine the coefficients of the linear terms <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>t</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>t</asciimath></stem> (in which the Bernoulli numbers occur), it must be possible to obtain the required relation by comparison of the respective coefficients.</p>

<p id="_2041301c-8939-877e-8c43-85302d3d6c49">Let us begin by decomposing the alternate sum <xref target="eq1"/> in a suitable way — the very  rearrangement we tried to avoid in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="muller" citeas="[1]"/>. Since <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>n</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>n</asciimath></stem> is even, we can put <stem block="false" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>n</mi>
    <mo>/</mo>
    <mn>2</mn>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mi>t</mi>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>n//2 = t</asciimath></stem>. Then</p>

<formula id="_50926f86-1d64-5e35-68d3-d4920e7c3bd1" anchor="eq6"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <msub>
      <mtext/>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msub>
    <msub>
      <mstyle mathvariant="double-struck">
        <mi>Z</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mi>n</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>t</mi>
      </munderover>
      <msup>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mn>2</mn>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </msup>
    </mrow>
    <mo>−</mo>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>t</mi>
      </munderover>
      <msup>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mn>2</mn>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>−</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </msup>
    </mrow>
  </mstyle>
</math><asciimath>""_rZZ_n = sum_(j=1)^t (2j)^r - sum_(j=1)^t (2j-1)^r</asciimath></stem></formula>

<formula id="_c24e040f-c92e-a60e-d8e6-bc7271555164" unnumbered="true"><stem block="true" type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
    <mo>=</mo>
    <msup>
      <mn>2</mn>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msup>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>t</mi>
      </munderover>
      <msup>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </msup>
    </mrow>
    <mo>−</mo>
    <msup>
      <mn>2</mn>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msup>
    <msup>
      <mrow>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mfrac>
          <mn>1</mn>
          <mn>2</mn>
        </mfrac>
        <mo>)</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mi>r</mi>
    </msup>
    <mrow>
      <munderover>
        <mo>∑</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mi>j</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mi>t</mi>
      </munderover>
      <mrow>
        <munderover>
          <mo>∑</mo>
